install nvm (node version manager)
The Node Version Manager (NVM) is a command-line utility used to manage and switch between multiple active versions of Node.js on a single system. Whether youâ€™re an admin or a developer, being able to change the javascript runtime environment on your system simplifies testing applications across different versions.


steps for installing nvm
- apt-get update -y
- apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev -y
- curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.34.0/install.sh | bash

steps for verify the installation
- nvm --version
- get all the commands of nvm 
nvm help


install node specific version nodejs version
list of all available nodejs version
nvm ls-remote  

install nodejs
nvm install 13

switch between nodejs versions
nvm install stable
nvm current
nvm use v13